  <h1 class="article-title">About</h1>
</header>

<div class="prose">
  <p>I'm Mani Kumar Kundurthi. I work in data science and quantitative modeling — currently building AI-driven dynamic pricing frameworks for commercial banking portfolios, covering segmentation, elasticity modeling, and constrained optimization.</p>

  <p>Outside of applied work, I spend time on mathematics (pure and applied), competitive programming, and software projects across a few different languages. This site is where I write things down as I learn them — mostly machine learning internals, coding notes, and math I wanted to actually understand rather than take for granted.</p>

  <p>Expect derivations, working code, and the occasional dead end left in on purpose.</p>

  <h2>What to expect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Machine learning</strong> — model internals, the math underneath common methods, and notes from working through things like ensemble methods, GAMs, and evaluation metrics.</li>
    <li><strong>Coding</strong> — implementation notes, small projects, and language exploration across Python, Go, and whatever else I'm poking at.</li>
    <li><strong>Math</strong> — pure and applied topics I wanted to actually derive rather than just cite, from linear algebra to the occasional recreational problem.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How this site works</h2>
  <p>No comments, no newsletter, no tracking. Articles are plain Markdown files with inline LaTeX rendered at build time. If something's wrong or unclear, feel free to reach out through any of the links below.</p>

